docs.abstract: Frank Bruni Op-Ed column examines lessons Democrats can draw from Republican Sen Rob Portman's re-election in Ohio to seat many thought Democrats would easily take back from GOP; suggests Portman prevailed because, unlike Democratic candidates nationwide, he maintained strict discipline in getting out simple message that he would work hard to address concerns of Ohio voters.
